Results\: Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching. 6085df94-1ab7-4e1e-a97f-695f8d274e78.be614a02-6085-4f8c-877f-15073322f991.description=ca766edc-07ab-4d10-b7a4-f3e2ee8a1e88.172c63d0-f5e2-452b-8257-28d1c3374f7a.description 6085df94-1ab7-4e1e-a97f-695f8d274e78.description=
 Purpose

This workflow will create a Weblogic Domain and Admin Server from an existing installation of Weblogic 11g or 12c.


 Results verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether the installation was successful. Be sure to also perform the following steps\:

   1. View the {DomainPath}/servers/AdminServer//logs/AdminServer.log file. This file is created when the Admin Server is started up, look for the following to see if the     Admin Server started up cleanly\:  Server started in RUNNING mode

 Notification plan

Define who should be notified when the workflow succeeds and fails.
 Required Inputs

    Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
    Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
    Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
    Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
    Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
    Admin Server Hostname - Required\: This is the hostname or ip address that the Admin Server will run on.
    Admin Server Name - Required\: Lable or name given to the Admin Server.
    Admin Server Port - Requried\: This will be the non ssl port that the Admin Server will run on.
    BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic.
    Domain Path - Required\: Fully qualified path that the domain and domain configuration will be created under. For example /opt/weblogic/user_projects/domains.
    Enable SSL - Required\:  This parameter will set the admin server to either use or not use the ssl port for communication.  Valid options are true or false.
    Hostname - Required\: Hostname used to start node manager.
    Server.Become User - No description
    Setup Custom SSL Stores - Required\: This parameter will set whether you want to run ssl with the demo ssl certificates or with your own custom keystore and truststore.  Options are true or false.  If true then the hidden parameters Custom KeyStore Path, Custom KeyStore PassPhrase, Custom Truststore Path, Custom TrustStore PassPhrase and Private Key Alias have to be set.
    Start Node Manager - Required\: Flag for starting the WebLogic Node Manager or not. Set this to True if you want the workflow to start the Weblogic Node Manager. False, otherwise.
    Weblogic Admin Password - Required\: This will be the password that will be used to authenticate with the Admin Server.
    WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/WebLogic/wlserver_10.3

 Optional Inputs

    Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
    Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
    Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
